    "created_at": "2016-05-10T16:46:59Z",
    "updated_at": "2016-05-10T16:46:59Z",
    "body": "To anyone coming across this. My initial hack doesn't work with more recent versions of Electron, I'm now using setTimeout to delay showing the window instead:\n\n``` js\nconst prefWindow = new BrowserWindow({\n  // ...\n});\n\nprefWindow.loadURL('prefs.html');\n\nprefWindow.webContents.on('did-finish-load', () => {\n  setTimeout(() => prefWindow.show(), 50); // HACK\n});\n```\n\nThis bug may be specific to my app and the way I'm doing things. Does anybody know when the window shadow is drawn? Is it after the `window.onload` event?\n"
  },
